TITLE: Executing NullAssertionInIfStatementCheck for Bug Prevention in Java
DESCRIPTION: Verifies that null checks (e.g., `variable != null`) are placed first within compound `if` statements (e.g., `if (variable != null && variable.method())`) to prevent potential NullPointerExceptions. This Bug Prevention check applies to `.java` files.
