TITLE: Directly Passing Arguments to ListUtil.fromArray in Java
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the preferred way to create a list from multiple elements using `ListUtil.fromArray` by passing the elements directly as varargs. This avoids the unnecessary explicit creation of a `new User[]` array. Assumes a `_getUser` method exists and returns a `User` object. Depends on Liferay's `ListUtil`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/liferay/liferay-portal/blob/master/modules/util/source-formatter/documentation/list_util.markdown#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
addUsers(
    ListUtil.fromArray(
        _getUser("Anthony"), _getUser("Belinda"), _getUser("Emily"),
        _getUser("Lucy")));
```

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
addUsers(
    ListUtil.fromArray(
        new User[] {
            _getUser("Anthony"), _getUser("Belinda"), _getUser("Emily"),
            _getUser("Lucy")
        }));
```

