TITLE: Simplifying Single-Element List Creation with ListUtil.fromArray in Java
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates using `ListUtil.fromArray` to create a List containing a single element obtained from `UserLocalServiceUtil.getUser(userId)`. This approach is more concise than manually creating an `ArrayList`, adding the single element, and then passing the list. This requires Liferay's `ListUtil` and `UserLocalServiceUtil` classes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/liferay/liferay-portal/blob/master/modules/util/source-formatter/documentation/list_util.markdown#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
addUsers(ListUtil.fromArray(UserLocalServiceUtil.getUser(userId)));
```

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
List<User> users = new ArrayList<>();

users.add(UserLocalServiceUtil.getUser(userId));

addUsers(users);
```

