TITLE: Refactored Early Return Pattern Without Else - Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet presents the recommended refactored approach by eliminating the redundant else branch. By placing the dependent action outside and after the early return, the code is more concise and easier to read. Requires the standard Java environment and a 'User' class. Input: takes a 'User' object. Output: void. This version never executes 'user.setActive(true);' if 'user.isActive()' is true, matching the intended control flow.
SOURCE: https://github.com/liferay/liferay-portal/blob/master/modules/util/source-formatter/src/main/resources/documentation/check/java_else_statement_check.markdown#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public void _activate(User user) {
    if (user.isActive()) {
        return;
    }

    user.setActive(true);
}
```

