TITLE: Non-Compliant List Nullity Check Placement - Java
DESCRIPTION: This Java snippet illustrates an incorrect ordering where list.isEmpty() is evaluated before confirming the List is not null, which can result in a NullPointerException. Standard Java libraries are used, with a List<String> parameter and a boolean return type. The key limitation is the risky method call prior to null verification, which this example intentionally demonstrates as a warning.
SOURCE: https://github.com/liferay/liferay-portal/blob/master/modules/util/source-formatter/src/main/resources/documentation/check/null_assertion_in_if_statement_check.markdown#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public boolean method1(List<String> list) {
	if (list.isEmpty() || (list == null)) {
		return false;
	}

	return true;
}
```

