TITLE: Iterating Over Primitive Arrays Using Index-Based For-Loop in Java
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet showcases a traditional index-based for-loop to traverse a long array, invoking a method on each element by referencing its index. The code depends on getUserIds() and deleteUser(long userId). Parameters: userIds is traversed using integer index i; userIds[i] is used in each iteration. Input: array from getUserIds(); Output: side-effect of deleteUser called on each element. Manual index management may be error-prone and is less readable compared to the enhanced for-loop.
SOURCE: https://github.com/liferay/liferay-portal/blob/master/modules/util/source-formatter/documentation/enhanced_for_loop.markdown#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
long[] userIds = getUserIds();

for (int i = 0; i < userIds.length; i++) {
    deleteUser(userIds[i]);
}
```

