TITLE: Redundant Log Level Check Example in Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates a redundant logging pattern that should be avoided. It first checks if DEBUG is enabled and logs the exception, then unnecessarily checks if WARN is enabled to log the *same* exception. If the intent is to log at the appropriate level, the logger framework handles this implicitly. This specific pattern of checking multiple levels sequentially for the same logging action is discouraged for being redundant and potentially inefficient.
SOURCE: https://github.com/liferay/liferay-portal/blob/master/modules/util/source-formatter/src/main/resources/documentation/check/redundant_log_check.markdown#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
if (_log.isDebugEnabled()) {
	_log.debug(exception);
}
else if (_log.isWarnEnabled()) {
	_log.warn(exception);
}
```

