TITLE: Configuring Dynamic Elements for Page Links in Liferay Portal XML
DESCRIPTION: This XML snippet defines dynamic elements for linking to different types of pages in Liferay Portal. It includes configurations for private and public layouts, some with specific group IDs. The 'link_to_layout' type is used with 'keyword' indexing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/liferay/liferay-portal/blob/master/modules/apps/export-import/export-import-test/src/testIntegration/resources/com/liferay/exportimport/internal/content/processor/test/dependencies/layout_links_user_group.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: XML
CODE:
```
<?xml version="1.0"?>

<root available-locales="en_US" default-locale="en_US">
	<dynamic-element name="link_to_page1" type="link_to_layout" index-type="keyword">
		<dynamic-content language-id="en_US"><![CDATA[[$LAYOUT_ID_PRIVATE$]@private]]></dynamic-content>
	</dynamic-element>
	<dynamic-element name="link_to_page2" type="link_to_layout" index-type="keyword">
		<dynamic-content language-id="en_US"><![CDATA[[$LAYOUT_ID_PRIVATE$]@private-user@[$GROUP_ID_PRIVATE$]]]></dynamic-content>
	</dynamic-element>
	<dynamic-element name="link_to_page3" type="link_to_layout" index-type="keyword">
		<dynamic-content language-id="en_US"><![CDATA[[$LAYOUT_ID_PUBLIC$]@public]]></dynamic-content>
	</dynamic-element>
	<dynamic-element name="link_to_page4" type="link_to_layout" index-type="keyword">
		<dynamic-content language-id="en_US"><![CDATA[[$LAYOUT_ID_PUBLIC$]@public@[$GROUP_ID_PUBLIC$]]]></dynamic-content>
	</dynamic-element>
</root>
```

